1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:05,045
He has carried a single black star since nineteen fifty-seven.

2
00:00:05,095 --> 00:00:09,340
The year a small nation looked the British Empire in the eye... and walked free.

3
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,490
Tonight, the empire talks back.

4
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:20,760
In episode seven, we predicted Brazil would beat Haiti four-one — but Haiti scored the goal of the night.

5
00:00:20,810 --> 00:00:25,070
Tonight... the colony meets the crown.

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,075
Welcome back to WorldCup twenty-six Legends, episode eight. England versus Ghana.

7
00:00:31,125 --> 00:00:35,200
Group L. Football's inventors against football's defiance.

8
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:44,690
And stay with me — because in the sixty-seventh minute of our story, one man throws his whole body across history.

9
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:50,575
First, the truth. Nineteen fifty-seven.

10
00:00:50,625 --> 00:00:54,700
Ghana becomes the FIRST nation south of the Sahara to win independence from Britain.

11
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:02,085
Fast forward. Twenty eleven. Wembley. England host Ghana for the very first time.

12
00:01:02,135 --> 00:01:07,220
Eighty thousand seats... and half of them turn red, gold and green.

13
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:13,675
England lead. Then, the ninety-first minute — Asamoah Gyan.

14
00:01:13,725 --> 00:01:18,900
The away team silences the home of football. One-one. Wembley belongs to Ghana.

15
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:24,630
And do not forget twenty-ten.

16
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:28,810
Ghana, seconds from becoming the first African team in a World Cup semifinal — denied by a hand on the line.

17
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:32,700
Tonight, for the very first time, they meet at a World Cup.

18
00:01:32,750 --> 00:01:35,950
The conversation finally happens on the biggest stage of all.

19
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,790
So meet the inventors — the men who gave the world this game.

20
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:47,090
Harry Kane.

21
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:49,730
England's greatest-ever scorer — still hunting the medal that completes him.

22
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:58,805
Jude Bellingham, the golden boy of Madrid, who plays like he was born for the biggest nights.

23
00:01:58,855 --> 00:02:04,160
Phil Foden bends reality. And Bukayo Saka — who turned cruelty into greatness.

24
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,820
Talent for a tournament. And a weight only England carries.

25
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,100
But Ghana did not come to play a supporting role.

26
00:02:17,150 --> 00:02:20,250
The Black Stars carry a whole continent's pride into the light.

27
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:27,275
Thomas Partey — the general.

28
00:02:27,325 --> 00:02:31,100
Years in the Premier League proving, over and over, that African footballers belong at the very top.

29
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:36,740
Inaki Williams, who chose Ghana over Spain.

30
00:02:36,790 --> 00:02:40,030
Antoine Semenyo, forged in the league England invented.

31
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:43,320
And young Issahaku — they whisper the name of Abedi Pele.

32
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,460
This is not an underdog. This is a reckoning.

33
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:54,205
And the duel inside the match: Bellingham against Partey. The heir to the throne...

34
00:02:54,255 --> 00:02:58,960
against the man who guards the gate. Heart against heart.

35
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:04,040
Our prediction — built on nineteen fifty-seven, on Wembley, and on one man on the line.

36
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:07,630
Watch closely.

37
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:12,225
Thirty-fourth minute. Foden threads it, Kane turns — finishes. One-nil England.

38
00:03:12,275 --> 00:03:16,000
The crown settles on its head.

39
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:21,950
But Ghana does not bow. They press. They believe. And the clock crawls toward...

40
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:26,050
the sixty-seventh minute.

41
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,340
Here it is. The moment we promised.

42
00:03:31,390 --> 00:03:35,730
Saka flies down the right, cuts it back — Kane rises — header, goalbound, surely two-nil —

43
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:40,490
The whole stadium holds its breath —

44
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,175
PARTEY! Off the line!

45
00:03:48,225 --> 00:03:51,400
The general throws his whole body across history and clears it! Ghana SURVIVES!

46
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:57,850
And then — the eighty-eighth minute. Just like twenty eleven. Ghana strike late.

47
00:03:57,900 --> 00:04:02,750
One-one. The Black Stars make the empire listen all over again.

48
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,285
Do you agree? Comment LIONS if England top Group L.

49
00:04:06,335 --> 00:04:09,120
Comment STARS if Ghana's draw shocks the world.

50
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:15,680
And the elder with the single black star?

51
00:04:15,730 --> 00:04:18,910
Legend number nine: the Keeper of fifty-seven.

52
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:22,140
He has stood for every Ghana side since freedom itself.

53
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:30,450
Tonight, he watched the empire answered. Collect him inside the game.

54
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,697
Which brings us to YOU.

55
00:04:35,747 --> 00:04:38,943
At WorldCup twenty-six dot world, pick three of the forty-eight nations — and every goal they score...

56
00:04:38,993 --> 00:04:42,190
scores for you.

57
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:48,870
Free to play. Live leaderboard. Underdogs pay triple — like Ghana tonight.

58
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:54,240
Hit like — send this to the friend who thinks they know who invented football.

59
00:04:54,290 --> 00:04:58,330
And subscribe: the legends are only beginning.

